adviseScripts.text: Rabbit in the mountains, rabbit in the meadow, where does the rabbit want to go?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Hiya, Rabbity! Where is the rabbit in this song going?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Naturally, rabbits prefer the hills.
It's searching for a happier world.
The hills?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: That sounds like a far-away place!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Come on, rabbit! I believe in you!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Whoa!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: She's really looking for a happier world!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: That's so cool!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Alice and I sing some songs and have a good time together.
Hey, Rabbity. I was wondering.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: What if Sleeping Beauty gets hungry while she's sleeping?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: She'll have plenty to feast on in her dreams.
If she gets hungry, she'll wake up.
Hey, you're right!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I never thought about all the great food in her dreams!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Now I don't have to worry about her anymore!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Really? She'll get up?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Then we'll need to have some food ready for her, right?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Hmm... that's a lot of work.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Alice and I have a serious conversation about Sleeping Beauty.
The Queen has brought soooooo much snow.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Is there a way we can ask her to stop?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: We could soothe her nerves with a cup of black tea.
Actually, the snow has nothing to do with Ludmilla.
You're right! If the Queen is in a good mood, she won't bring any more snow!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: You're a genius!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Really? How can that be?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Oh no! Does this mean the Queen is losing control of her powers?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: This is no good. No good at all!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Alice and I chat about Ludmilla for a while.
Speaking of carrots,
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: which taste do you prefer – sweet or salty?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Actually, I don't like carrots at all.
I like salty-sweet carrots.
Really?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: So strange...
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I thought carrots were every rabbit's favorite food!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Salty-sweet?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I never knew there were salty-sweet carrots!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I bet they taste soooo good!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I discuss the flavors of carrots with Alice.
Rabbity!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I heard that people in the Ark eat some kind of food called Splendamin.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: What makes Splendamin so splendid?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: It puts you in a splendid mood.
It gives you a splendid body.
Splendid mood?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: That's amazing! A splendid mood!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Amazing!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Body?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Wow! So, you must have a splendid body, too!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I have a good talk with Alice about Splendamin.
Speaking of weather,
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: what kind of weather do you prefer: sunny or snowy?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Sunny.
Snowy.
I like sunny days too,
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: but I like snowy days more!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: That's because our Queen is the Snow Queen!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I love our Queen's snow as well!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: The snow is cold, and it can be really scary sometimes...
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: But I love it anyway! It's the same color as our Queen.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I have a good talk with Alice about the Snow Queen.
Rabbity!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Why don't the Queen of Hearts' minions need to sleep?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I don't think I've ever seen them go to sleep, not even once.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: They're under an insomnia spell.
That's why we have to make them all go to sleep.
Ooh... really?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: The Queen of Hearts' minions are all big meanies,
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: but I still feel sorry for them.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: You're right! If they can't go to sleep by themselves...
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: We can give them a little help!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: You're a real genius!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I have a good talk with Alice about the minions of the Queen of Heart, Raptures.
Rabbit in the mountains, oh, come drink by the spring.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Rabbit in the morning, rubbing its eyes.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Oh! Rabbit! Do you always wake up this early?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: That's right! I'm gonna go drink some spring water.
I was just sleepwalking.
Whoa! Early birds are the best!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: From now on, I'll wake up early with you! I promise!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Mmm-hmm. Sounds fishy to me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: How did you go to the spring
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: if you were sleepwalking?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I have a discussion on the way to the spring with Alice for a while.
Rabbity, the fat's in the fire!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: The Queen is so powerful that the machines have been taken down one after another!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I don't know what to do.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Let them stay hidden.
They will be fine as long as you stay with Ludmilla all the time.
That won't do at all.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I've tried that long ago,
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: but the Queen told me that, it would be more difficult to rescue the lost princess.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Ok! I will!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: After all, I like being with her.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I have a discussion about rescuing the machines with Alice for a while.
Hey, Rabbity! Don't fall asleep in the middle of a race!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Remember?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I won't take part in any race.
OK. I will try my best in every race.
Huh? Why not?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Have you quit racing?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Hmph. Good!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I'll be your number one fan.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I'll watch you win all the races!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I chat with Alice about how to beat tortoises in a race.
Hey Rabbity!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Whenever you sleep, do you dream?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Not very often.
All the time.
Darn, that's too bad.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: If you did, I was going to ask what you dreamed about.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: So you're just like me!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I dream all the time about you and I running around
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: in a field of flowers together, without a care in the world.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: What do you dream about?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Alice and I talk about dreams.
The snow is really piling up today!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: What do you like to do whenever it snows?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Have a snowball fight.
Make a snowman.
Wow, that sounds cool!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I've never done that before.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Wanna have a snowball fight with me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I wanted to do something a little different today,
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: but since you really enjoy making snowmen...
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I can make another one.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Alice and I try and come up with other snow-related activities.
Doo dah, doo dee dah...
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Rabbity, sing with me!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Join in and complement her singing.
Sing along jokingly.
Whoa!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: You sing so well!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Sing it again!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Hmm, that doesn't quite gel...
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Still, I'm glad to see you enjoying yourself.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Alice and I have fun singing together.
You must have other animal friends, right?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: What other animal friends are you close with?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: A tortoise.
A dog.
Wait, rabbits and tortoises don't get along!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: They had that big disagreement over that race...
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Oh, so you have a dog friend?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: What's its name?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Poli.
Hey, I know a policewoman with the same name!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Alice and I have a conversation about animal friends.
Hey Rabbity!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Have you ever eaten snow before?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Sure, I've eaten snow that's fallen on the ground.
Never.
Wow!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I've only had snow that's coming down from the sky.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I wonder if it tastes any different once it's hit the ground.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Let's try some next time we run across it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I can't believe you still haven't tried it!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: You can't eat snow once it melts,
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: so make sure you try it before then.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Alice and I talk about the taste of snow.
I'm in the mood for cotton candy today.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Do you like cotton candy, Rabbity?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I like it because it's sweet.
Not really, I think it's too sweet.
I figured you would!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Let's have some together next time.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I want some that are pink-colored!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: But that's why I like it so much...
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I guess you don't have a big sweet tooth.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Alice and I talk about cotton candy.
Whenever I can't fall asleep,
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I imagine you and I are having tea time, Rabbity.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: What goes through your mind when you can't fall asleep?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I imagine tea time with you.
I lay down and try to keep my mind blank.
Wow, so we've been thinking about the same thing!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Hopefully we can run into each other in our dreams.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I'll be sure to prepare some scrumptious treats for you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Don't you get bored just laying down not thinking about anything?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: It'd be more fun
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: if you tried to imagine something...
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Alice and I talk about imagination.
I'm making cookies with the Queen today!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I'll give you some once I finish.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: What should I make them look like?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Like a rabbit.
Like a snowman.
Whoa, freaky!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I was thinking the exact same thing!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Our minds are in sync.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I'll try and make it extra delicious for you!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I thought you'd want it to be shaped like a rabbit...
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: But I can try and go for a snowman.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I eagerly anticipated trying Alice's delicious cookies.
Rabbity!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Would a cloud melt like cotton candy does?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Sure, and it would probably taste the same as well.
I doubt it.
So it'd taste similar as well?!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: That'd be amazing!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I hope I can try eating some actual clouds one day.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Really?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Oh, I thought they'd be similar...
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Alice and I converse about clouds.
Hey Rabbity!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: If you were the main character in a movie, what would you be?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: A hatmaker.
Alice.
I think you'd make a great hatmaker!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: You and I could have a tea party every day.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: We'd have so much fun!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Uh... but Alice is who I want to be...
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: What about another role?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Alice and I fantasize about being movie protagonists.
